"It's truly heartbreaking when one of our fellow Night Hawks
gets killed... It's not like anyone gains anything from
killing us..."

"Since then, there haven't been any more incidents of Night
Hawks being killed. Maybe the culprit was caught without us
knowing. Now we can work with peace of mind."
Ahn! It's being stirred up inside me...\I[15]

(...It would be bad to interrupt. I should move away from
here...)

Ahn! It feels like it's being stirred up inside my
belly...\I[15]
(...I shouldn't interrupt. Let's move away from here...)

Isn't that Karin? What are you doing out here in the middle
of the night?
Wha-!? You're not from Tomichouya...!? Why are you here?

It's nothing--this shack, I owned it two years ago. It's
right next to the mansion and has been making a racket every
night, so I came to complain this evening.

Ugh...! (Tomichouya used to be the landlord? I had no
idea...)

I heard it went from a freak show to a small theater...
could it be... Karin, are you the current owner?

...Yes, that's right. Is there a problem? I paid a large sum
of 15,000 mon to the owner of the freak show to buy this
shack! Don't pick a fight with me, okay?

No, no, there's a big problem. That owner, he hasn't paid me
half of the shack's price. He borrowed 50,000 mon and still
owes it.

Didn't you ask for details when you bought it? Hahahaha!
Think about it, this is Nihonbashi, right? Even a shack
can't be bought for a mere 15,000 mon. He sold it and ran
off without telling you about the debt he owes me!

Becoming the owner of real estate naturally means inheriting
its debts as well. Now, how about you pay me the 50,000 mon
right now?

(What should I do...! I can't come up with such a large sum
all of a sudden...)

...What's with that look? You don't have the cash on hand?
Well, can't be helped. If you entertain me with a dance and
make me happy, I'll consider the shack's debt cleared.

Yes. Oh, I forgot to mention. The condition is that after
showing me the dance, you let me embrace you. How about it,
Karin\I[15]

...I understand. Then please come inside the theater. I'll
show you the dance... that's fine, right?

Ho! Really!? Alright! I'm looking forward to being
entertained Wahahaha!

Come on, stop laughing so loudly and hurry up and come in...
It's late at night and everyone's asleep... You're being a
nuisance to the neighbors.

What's this? Have you forgotten the promise we made at the
mansion? I am Karin's husband. You better bow your head
and treat me more politely--let's start over again. You need
to be more respectful\I[15]

...Please come in, my lord, into the theater...(Damn it,
this is humiliating...)

--Karin bowed her head to Tomichouya and led him into the
theater.

...I refuse. I didn't know anything about it. You should
claim the loaned money from the previous owner.

Why glare at me with such fierce eyes... Well, alright. If
you want to accept my terms, come talk to me again. Okay?
